Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Technician 1 North Vancouver , BC Description Competition Number S181027P Position Title Library Technician 1 Position Number S99971 Employee Group Staff Position Status Temporary Full-Time Start Date 10/02/2023 End Date (if applicable) 12/22/2023 Department Library Additional Notes Location North Vancouver Working with us Capilano University Library is seeking a library technician to join our team at our North Vancouver Campus. Working with students, staff, faculty, community borrowers, and supporting library services, you will be part of an integrated team that works in alignment with the library’s vision in providing services, resources, and spaces to spark the imagination and creativity of our community, and to support our students to engage as global citizens. For more information on the Library’s Vision, Purpose, and Values visit https://library.capilanou.ca/about-the-library/lib... Take a virtual tour of our campus here: https://capilanou.ca/programs—courses/get-started/... What you’ll do You will report to the University Librarian and receive direction from the Library Services Supervisor. At CapU Library, your work will encompass a combination of duties that support the ongoing needs of library services. This work will support communications such as maintaining the Library’s digital signage system and creating digital content and graphics as well as physical signage and displays and editing the library website. The position will support social media and outreach activities as well as working at the Library Services Desk. You will also collaborate with your colleagues and interact with students, faculty, and members of the community and provide referral and information services such as locating print and digital resources, circulating materials, creating user accounts, providing printing technical support, handling payments, maintaining patron and item records, and performing closing duties. CapU Library is seeking a team member who: is curious/inquisitive takes responsibility for their work enjoys working with people of diverse backgrounds and perspectives communicates effectively in groups and individually is a critical thinker has a willingness to learn is familiar with library trends and technology is able to adapt to change The applicant should have experience with: Information organization and retrieval in a library environment Integrated Library Systems (ILS) – (Capilano University Library uses Sierra) Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Publisher, Outlook &amp; PowerPoint) Graphical design platforms such as Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Acrobat, Adobe Illustrator and Microsoft Publisher Social media platforms such as Instagram, Twitter and Facebook What you’ll bring - Library Technician Diploma from a recognized post-secondary institution. - One year of relevant library experience. For more information For more information, please see the complete job description. Benefits At Capilano University, we understand that there is more to life than work. That is why we offer comprehensive benefits and support to help you and your family live a balanced life. Take a sneak peek to see what it is like to work at Capilano University. Posting Detail Information Days and Hours of Work Our standard work week is 35 hours per week. Monday – Thursday, 2:30 p.m. – 10 p.m. Friday, 10:30 a.m. – 6:00 p.m. Bridge Period (if applicable) Pay Group 14 Salary $3,723 per month based on 35 hours per week (with increments up to $4,186 per month) Union MoveUP Job Open Date 08/16/2023 Job Close Date 08/25/2023 Open Until Filled No Quick Link for Posting https://jobs-capilanou.peopleadmin.com/postings/6040 Supplemental QuestionsRequired fields are indicated with an asterisk (*).* Have you completed a two-year Library Technology diploma comparable to the programs offered at Langara College and University of the Fraser Valley?YesNo* Do you have one year of relevant library experience?YesNoApplicant DocumentsRequired DocumentsResumeCover LetterOptional DocumentsTranscriptsLetter of RecommendationProof of Educationhttps://jobs-capilanou.peopleadmin.com/postings/6040 Compensation $3,723 per month based on 35 hours per week (with increments up to $4,186 per month) Closes: 25 August, 2023 Capilano University North Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
