Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Deputy Chief Librarian Edmonton , AB Description Deputy Chief LibrarianLM Vice Provost Lib MuseumsCompetition No. - A101751651Closing Date - Will remain open until filled.The University of Alberta Library seeks applicants to serve as its next Deputy Chief Librarian. Reporting to the Vice-Provost (Library and Museums) and the Chief Librarian, the Deputy will join an experienced and capable leadership team guiding one of Canada’s premier research libraries. Central to the Deputy’s work is the opportunity to infuse all our work with the Library’s commitment to equity, diversity, inclusion, and accessibility as well as to facilitate our path with indigenization and decolonization. The Deputy directs the Library’s strategic planning processes, which we have designed to increase staff participation in all phases. The Deputy plays a major role in helping Librarians build meaningful careers in the Library and serves as the primary contact for matters related to collective agreements and librarian roles, including oversight of hiring and tenure processes and representing the Library in bargaining. The Deputy also provides leadership for the Library’s administrative functions as well as for its communications.The University of Alberta has taken significant steps in recent years toward becoming a more inclusive and progressive institution. In 2022, the University launched its first Indigenous strategic plan, Braiding Past, Present, and Future. In the same year, the institution created the Office of the Vice-Provost for Equity, Diversity, and Inclusion. The Vice-Provost EDI is now leading a revision of our 2019 Strategic Plan for EDI and recently announced the University’s first Academic Lead on Equity Praxis and Systemic Ableism. The Library’s strategic priorities reflect this commitment and direction; it’s an exciting time to join us in this work.The University of Alberta Library is one of Canada’s leading research libraries with a strong reputation for innovation and collaboration. We have seven distinct library locations on four campuses, three in Edmonton and one in Camrose. These include a state-of-the-art high-density storage facility opened in 2018 and a brand new Health Sciences Library opening in September 2023. Our collection is one of Canada’s largest and includes extensive special collections and the University Archives. The Library is part of a broader Library &amp; Museums portfolio, providing opportunities for collaboration between the Library, the Museums, and the University of Alberta Press.While the library facilities and collections are impressive, it is the staff working here who make it both a leading library as well as an excellent place to work and build a career. As part of a large university, we engage in a wide range of campus initiatives across the entire spectrum of disciplines. At the regional and national level, the Library contributes to myriad collaborative initiatives in all areas of library work, often providing leadership for new and key initiatives. The Deputy plays a key role in guiding and shaping the recruitment and development of our staff, maintaining our excellent service to the institution and the broader community while ensuring that the library continues to be an excellent and inclusive workplace where staff can build careers.The Deputy supervises the Administrative Services Manager, a senior position that directs the administrative functions of the portfolio office; the Deputy may also supervise senior librarian positions outside of the leadership team based on current needs.The successful candidate will be able to show evidence of significant engagement and experience in libraries. Ideally, candidates will have experience in a variety of library roles and a broad understanding of the current role of large research libraries. In our organization, important assets are creativity, vision, critical thinking, and a proven ability to lead and inspire others. Paramount is a strong commitment to supporting our goal to foster and sustain an inclusive and equitable workplace and culture. A master’s degree in library science from an ALA-accredited institution or equivalent is required.This position is in accordance with University terms and conditions, and remuneration will be commensurate with qualifications, experience, and will be competitive with public research post-secondary institutions. The position is based on a five-year term with the possibility of renewal and a tenured position as a Librarian 3. Components of compensation will include base salary, a comprehensive benefits package, as well as additional negotiated benefits applicable to the position.Applications should consist of a cover letter, curriculum vitae, and the names of three references. This position will remain open until filled; review of applications will begin September 1, 2023.How to ApplyApply OnlineNote: Online applications are accepted until midnight Mountain Standard Time of the closing date.All qualified candidates are encouraged to apply; however, Canadians and permanent residents will be given priority. If suitable Canadian citizens or permanent residents cannot be found, other individuals will be considered. The University of Alberta is committed to an equitable, diverse, and inclusive workforce. We welcome applications from all qualified persons. We encourage women; First Nations, Métis and Inuit persons; members of visible minority groups; persons with disabilities; persons of any sexual orientation or gender identity and expression; and all those who may contribute to the further diversification of ideas and the University to apply. Compensation Librarian 3 range ($103,644 - $172,206) Closes: 14 November, 2023 University of Alberta Libraries Edmonton , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
