Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Services &amp; Support Associate – Discovery &amp; Access Toronto , ON Description Services &amp; Support Associate – Discovery &amp; AccessFull-Time Permanent PositionOntario Colleges Library Service (OCLS)Job TypeFull-time (37.5 hours/week) permanent positionOur OrganizationOntario Colleges Library Service (OCLS) is a not-for-profit organization funded by the Ministry of Colleges and Universities to support Ontario’s 24 publicly assisted colleges and their libraries. With OCLS’s strong reputation for service excellence, the college libraries trust us to deliver services and expertise in line with our mandate to create efficiencies, achieve cost savings, and build capacity across the system.Our reputation would not have been built, nor could it be maintained, without the skills, knowledge, and experience of the extraordinary members of the OCLS team. Be part of our close-knit, collaborative team and join us in delivering quality shared services to Ontario’s college library system.To learn more about our mission, values and services, visit the OCLS website or view our Strategic Plan.Your OpportunityThe Ontario college libraries have recently implemented the Ex Libris Alma/Primo VE library services platform. With all 24 college libraries running the same library management system and discovery service for the first time in history, there are exciting opportunities for synergies and shared services that OCLS and the colleges are keen to leverage.In this role, you will use your library training and strong service orientation to optimize discovery of the colleges’ e-resource collections for over 200,000 college students and staff across the province.This position is an excellent opportunity for a customer-focused, self-directed, and tech-savvy library professional with a solid foundation and interest in e-resources discovery and access, library systems, and metadata standards. As a key member of the OCLS team, you’ll collaborate closely with dedicated colleagues who support each other to meet the needs of our college clients.Key Responsibilities Respond to service requests related to e-resources in Alma/Primo VE, including troubleshooting and researching access issues, evaluating records in the Community Zone (CZ), and testing and setting up new products in the Alma Network Zone (NZ). Create, edit, distribute, and maintain shared metadata for e-resource collections across the college system. Monitor internal and external listservs and other communication channels to identify and act on relevant information as it emerges. Lead the development and distribution of customer-facing communications related to e-resources in Alma/Primo including emails to listservs and distribution groups, website updates, instructional materials, and other documentation. Participate on and support committees and working groups related to e-resources in Alma/Primo, including researching and preparing briefing notes, and facilitating group discussions to support decision-making. Evaluate existing workflows and design new workflows, with an eye towards efficiency and consistency. Develop and maintain internal documentation on workflows, procedures, and practices to support business continuity, cross-training, and efficient operations. Participate in additional services and projects as assigned.What You’ll NeedWork Experience and Training Post-secondary diploma from a Library &amp; Information Technician program or related discipline or an equivalent combination of experience and education; a Bachelor’s degree is an asset. 1-2 years’ experience working in or with libraries. Demonstrated experience providing outstanding customer service.Technical Skills and Experience Familiarity with library systems and tools, such as integrated library systems (ILS) and/or library services platforms (LSP), discovery layers, and/or link resolver tools. Knowledge of MARC and RDA standards.General Skills and Attributes Demonstrated ownership and pride in the quality of customer service provided to internal and external customers. Excellent research, problem solving, and analytical skills, with the ability to develop creative solutions. Superior organizational and administrative skills, with the ability to manage priorities and meet deadlines with minimal supervision. Effective communication and active listening skills, with the ability to synthesize and present complex or ambiguous information clearly and concisely. Strong interpersonal skills, with the ability to build excellent working relationships with peers, customers and service providers. Aptitude for and keen interest in learning the latest information, collaboration, and communication technologies. Ability to work well both independently and collaboratively within a team. Detail-oriented, accurate, thorough, and efficient. Experience with Office 365 collaboration tools (e.g., SharePoint, OneDrive, Teams) and content management systems (e.g., LibGuides, Confluence).Asset QualificationsThe qualifications listed below are highly desirable but not necessarily mandatory and should be explicitly described in your cover letter: Experience in an academic library, in library systems, or in a library consortium setting. Familiarity with the e-resource management lifecycle, particularly related to discovery and access. Experience with the Ex Libris Alma/Primo VE Library Services Platform (LSP) software. Familiarity with authentication tools such as EZProxy. Experience creating and maintaining database records, database reporting, and/or manipulating data in Excel. Experience liaising with third-party service providers. Experience writing communications and documentation for diverse audiences. Fluency in French.What OCLS Offers Competitive compensation commensurate with experience; the salary range for this position begins at $55,662 annually Hybrid work environment Learning and development opportunities Comprehensive health and dental benefits, including vision care, massage therapy, acupuncture, psychotherapy and more CAAT Pension Plan Commitment to work-life balance, which includes: A minimum of 3 weeks of vacation per year, a summer earned days off program, and generous personal leave Employee and family assistance program (EFAP)Additional InformationOCLS welcomes applications from those who would contribute to the further diversification of our staff, including, but not limited to, Indigenous Peoples, persons with disabilities, and persons of any sexual orientation or gender identity, ethnicity, or age.OCLS is an equal opportunity employer and strives to ensure that its hiring process meets the needs of all persons with disabilities. As such, OCLS will provide reasonable accommodation for any applicant, as requested during the hiring process.Application DeadlineApplications must be received by 5:00 pm on Monday, August 28. Applications are reviewed as received.Position Start DateSeptember 2023How to ApplyInterested candidates may apply by sending a letter of application, current resumé and three references in a single file named “YourName_#163” via e-mail to applications@ocls.ca. Please quote “YourName - #163” in the subject line.We thank all candidates for their interest; however, only those candidates selected for interview will be contacted.This job posting is also available on our website. Compensation Competitive compensation commensurate with experience; the salary range for this position begins at $55,662 annually Closes: 28 August, 2023 Ontario Colleges Library Service Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
