Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? 1 Permanent Full Time Librarian Woodstock , ON Description Summary:Responsible to the Director, Staff Development and Professional Practice of Woodstock Hospital, the Librarian provides professional reference and collection access services and manages the hospital library.The Librarian also plans, develops, markets, coordinates, administers, reports, and evaluates the provision of library services (both reference and technical) and library resources to contracted organizations.Library services exist to assist clients in finding answers and retrieving evidence-based information related to patient care, institutional operation, staff education, and training. Travel is required between organizations and for off-site meetings.Qualifications: EDUCATION: Masters degree from an accredited program of the American Library Association EXPERIENCE: At least one year experience in a hospital or other health sciences library.Excellent knowledge of Library and Information Sciences theories, principles, and practices.Advanced knowledge of cataloguing principles and procedures NLM Classification and MeSH systems.Advanced knowledge of the biomedical literature and how to apply new related technologies.Advanced knowledge and demonstrated proficiency of reference services and online resources.Ability to provide information, which is evidence-based, current, comprehensive, and value-added.Ability to analyze client information needs critically and logically.Ability to successfully coordinate multiple projects in various sites simultaneously.Capacity to work and communicate effectively with all levels of medical and hospital staff at all sites.Ability to work independently with minimal direction and maximum communication.Works well under the pressure of multiple deadlines.Demonstrates a commitment to serving the information needs of health professionals with a strong public service orientation. SKILLS: Proficiency in use of computers and library technologies with proven experience in making effective use of electronic resources, integrated library systems, and LibGuidesStrong knowledge of research methodologies, Boolean searching, and Copyright LawExpertise in online searching, subject analysis, and critical appraisal of the literatureProgram development and fiscal management skills.Demonstrated skill in both oral and written communications.Skill in problem-solving and conflict resolution.Skill in motivating and working effectively with staff, clients, teams, and colleagues.Specialized subject knowledge appropriate to the business of the organization.Ability to prioritize and batch service requests, and work independently.Ability to analyze, evaluate, implement and use new technologies and tools.Experience designing and maintaining web pages.Knowledge of Microsoft Office products.Understand and support evidence-based practice.Develop an approach to planning, economies, and time management that incorporates a balance of personal and professional goals.Commitment to Patient Care &amp; Safety and Service Excellence.How to Apply:Please go to our Woodstock Hospital career page and apply for the job from there:Woodstock Hospital - 1 Permanent Full Time Librarian (njoyn.com)Woodstock Hospital:Located in the heart of Oxford County and serving more than 110,000 people, Woodstock Hospital is committed to promoting compassionate and respectful patient care. Join the team at our new state-of-the-art 178 bed hospital. We are a smoke-free and fragrance-free facility. Woodstock Hospital is also dedicated to sustaining a supportive environment and providing employment equity by meeting the accessibility needs of people with disabilities. Woodstock Hospital and its employees are committed to participating and complying with the by-laws and guidelines of the standards developed under the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act, 2005 (AODA). Compensation 62,556 to 73,690.5 Closes: 20 August, 2023 Woodstock Hospital Woodstock , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
