Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Service Desk Coordinator Camrose , AB Description Description: The Camrose Public Library is looking for an enthusiastic, versatile, customer service superstar to help our community and staff with all of their information needs. Job Summary: The Camrose Public Library is located in the city of Camrose Alberta, and serves a population of ~20,000, not including members of the Camrose County. CPL is a part of the Parkland Regional Library System. We need someone who is passionate about building positive community connections, who pays amazing attention to detail and can quickly adapt to whatever challenge is thrown their way. The right person for this job thrives on working with people of all ages and backgrounds, and communicates well with everyone. If you love solving a good puzzle and can effectively manage competing priorities, this job is for you. You will spend most of your time at the service desk where you will check items in and out, answer reference questions and reader’s advisory queries, book and invigilate exams, and connect patrons to CPL programming and services. Additionally, you will help administer payroll for the organization, assist the Manager with reporting, and schedule the circulation staff. You will be a key point of contact for the programmers, seasonal staff, volunteers, the manager and the director, helping all areas of the organization to work better together. Other circulation duties and occasional programming assistance will also be a part of the position. Duties and Responsibilities Include: Administer payroll with the ManagerAssist the Manager with reportingSchedule the circulation staffLiaise with Director, Manager, Programmers, Seasonal staff and Volunteers to aid in communicationAssist with signage while adhering to the Brand GuidelinesInteract with patrons to provide outstanding customer service Check-in/check-out materials Answer Reference questions including questions on e-resources and other technologyAnswer Reader’s Advisory questions Assist patrons on Public Computer stations as neededHelp coordinate, train and advise volunteers as neededAssist with Programming and Events as neededAssist with staff training as neededAssist with weeding the collection according to CPL proceduresAssist with collection development and ordering according to CPL proceduresProcess hold and transit materialsBook and invigilate exams according to library procedureBook Meeting Rooms according to library procedureReconcile cash register as neededPerform other related duties as required. Minimum Qualifications: Library and Information Technology Diploma strongly preferred, equivalent experience will be considered for the right candidateExperience with technologyExperience and comfort working with all ages.Reliable means of transportation.Fluent in written and spoken English.If chosen as successful candidate, must provide a current Police Check and Child Intervention Record Check every 3 years. Physical Requirements: Able to stand, walk or sit for long periods of time.Can climb, reach, stoop and kneel.Able to carry materials weighing up to 25 pounds.Manual dexterity to operate keyboards and library equipment.Speech and hearing sufficient to interact with patrons and read computer screens and fine text.Able to perform repetitive hand, arm, and body movements.Able to push a loaded book cart. Assets: Experience with scheduling.Experience in payroll.Fluency in languages other than English.Thirty-five (35) hours per week.May require rotating evening and weekend shifts. Hours of Work: Compensation: The hourly wage for this role ranges from $21.32 to $26.41 Supervisor: Manager of Library Services – Cheryl Hamel How to Apply: Please submit your cover letter and resume by clicking this link and selecting “Apply” by August 21, 2023, at 9:00am. Camrose Public Library celebrates diversity, and we are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. If you have a disability and need any accommodations through the recruitment and selection process, please reach out to cpl@prl.ab.ca Please direct any questions to the Interim Director, Jennifer McDevitt at jmcdevitt@prl.ab.ca Compensation $21.32 to $26.41 Closes: 21 August, 2023 Camrose Public Library Camrose , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
