Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Technician Lacombe , AB Description Library Technician - Full Time - Mary C. Moore Public Library, Lacombe, AlbertaMary C. Moore Public Library is seeking a full-time library technician to join our library team. 30 hours per week plus vacation, benefits and pension plan. Position Summary: The Library Technician shall guide and encourage patrons of all ages in the use of books and other materials at the library and serve the community as a specialist of library services. This position oversees the Interlibrary Loans, as well as the Periodical Collection and collaborates with the Head Librarian for Collection Development/Maintenance. Performs complex tasks involved with the computerized transactions of library materials to the public. The position requires excellent public service skills and strong organizational skills. This description does not necessarily include all of the essential functions that may be assigned to this position and is based upon the continuing needs of the organization.Qualifications &amp; Education Requirements: Library and Information Technology Diploma required.1-year experience of library work preferred.Experience working with the Dewey Decimal Classification System.Basic computer skills at minimum, advanced computer skills preferred.Experience in Microsoft Suite of Products, especially Microsoft Excel. Valid Alberta Driver’s License. Working Conditions: Work environment is typically sitting in an office setting and standing at a public service desk. Frequent sustained operation of office equipment is required. Position may require working evenings and weekends. Willingness to work outside normal business hours and travel on occasion. Complete job description will be sent upon request. Knowledge, Skills and Abilities: Knowledge of the policies, procedures, and activities of the Library and the City as they pertain to the performance of duties relating to the job. Effectively communicate and interact with staff in a professional and respectful manner, establish and maintain effective working relationships, with supervisors, members of the general public and all other groups involved in the activities of the library. Assemble information and make written reports and documents in a concise, clear, and effective manner. Use independent judgment and work with little direct supervision when necessary. Must learn and use the library computer system, hardware, and specialized software with high degree of efficiency. Excellent written and oral communication skills. Hourly wage: $22.37 - $29.36 plus vacation pay, pension and benefits. Position is 30 hours per week.Please submit cover letter and resume to:Mary C. Moore Public Librarymcmpl@prl.ab.ca by emailor can be dropped off in person at:101-5214 50th Avenue Lacombe, Alberta T4L 0B6 No phone calls please. You will only be contacted if you are granted an interview for the position.Position will remain open until a suitable candidate is found. Compensation $22.37 - $29.36 Closes: 6 November, 2023 Mary C. Moore Public Library Lacombe , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
